<p>The markup extension that brought me to ask this is Catel's <code>LanguageBinding</code>.</p>  <p>I was until now using <a href="http://www.codeproject.com/Articles/35159/WPF-Localization-Using-RESX-Files" rel="nofollow">Infralution's localization assembly</a>, which works more or less the same way.</p>  <p><strong>Catel</strong>:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;TextBlock Text="{LanguageBinding MyText}"/&gt; </code></pre>  <p><strong>Infralution</strong>:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;TextBlock Text="{Resx MyText}"/&gt; </code></pre>  <p>But as you can see, the markup extension is way shorter to write, thus less prone to typos.</p>  <p><strong>So I wanted to know if there was any way to be able to use LanguageBinding with another markup extension word</strong>, like:</p>  <p><strong>Ideal</strong>:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;TextBlock Text="{LB MyText}"/&gt; </code></pre>  <p><em>I'm well aware of readability issues and such, it's an example.</em></p>